 SINP-TNP/03-08 
Near-Horizon States of Black Holes and  Calogero Models 

B Basu-Mallick, Pijush K. Ghosh and Kumar S. Gupta(Talk
delivered by Kumar S. Gupta)  
Theory Division,

Saha Institute of Nuclear Physics,

1/AF Bidhannagar, Kolkata - 700064. 

 
We find self-adjoint extensions of the rational 
Calogero model in presence of the harmonic interaction. The corresponding
eigenfunctions may describe the near-horizon quantum states of certain types
of black holes.

03.65.-w, 04.70.Dy 
Calogero model, Self-adjoint extension, Black Holes 
	The dynamics of particles or fields in the near-horizon region of
black holes is often described in terms of the
Calogero Model. In particular, it has been shown that the
existence of the near-horizon conformal symmetry as well as
the logarithmic correction to the black hole entropy can be
described in terms of the self-adjoint extension of the 
Calogero model in absence of the confining potential. 
On the other hand, it has been argued that in certain
string theoretic description of black holes, the near-horizon dynamics is
governed by a many particle Calogero model in presence of the confining
potential.
It is therefore of interest to find the quantum states of this
model in presence of the self-adjoint extension. These states would be
expected to encode the dynamics for such black holes. A more detailed
description of the analysis presented below can be found in Ref.
.

