intersection of  with the horizontal straight line.
Note that the spectrum
generically consists of infinite number of positive energy solutions and at
most one negative energy solution.

2) Contrary to the spectrum of the rational Calogero model, 
the energy spectrum obtained from Eqn. () is not equispaced for
finite
values of  and for generic values of . 
This may seem surprising with the presence of  as
the spectrum generating algebra in this system, which demands 
that the eigenvalues be evenly spaced. However, when , ,
the generator of dilatations does not in
general leave the domain of the Hamiltonian invariant
. Consequently,  cannot be implemented as
the spectrum generating algebra except for , .


	It is plausible that the eigenfunctions described above would
describe the near-horizon quantum states of certain types of black holes as
described in Ref.. Calculation for the corresponding density of
states and entropy would be of future interest. 


